arators.\n\n```\nparam node\n\nNode representing and including breadcrumb component.\n\nparam base_url\n\nBase URL of site.\n\nparam max_search_depth\n\nMax depth for searching anchors.\n\nreturn\n\nTuple with breadcrumb items.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._parse_breadcrumb_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Split extracted name into left separator, clean name and right separator."]}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._postprocess_breadcrumbs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "breadcrumbs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "markup_hier", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "separators", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Post-process breadcrumbs using the following procedures:\n* If there is only a single breadcrumb with name and without link, try to\nsplit the name into separate breadcrumb items.\n* If markup exists, then use it for selecting correct breadcrumb items.\n* Otherwise, use location of separators to determine which breadcrumb items\nare relevant and which not (if there is separator between two items then\nthese two items are relevant)."]}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._postprocess_using_markup", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "breadcrumbs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "markup_hier", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._postprocess_using_separators", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "breadcrumbs", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "separators", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._extract_markup_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._remove_duplicated_first_and_last_items", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "breadcrumbs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Remove \"go back\" urls from the beginning or the end of breadcrumb\nelement.\nThere is an assumption that there can be only one such url.\nFirst it tries to remove url at the beginning by checking if there\nis any other the same url in further breadcrumb items. If not, it\nchecks the last url by comparing it with remaining urls."]}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._has_special_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "class_attr", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Check if a given value of class attribute has a class that relates to\ndrop down like \"dropdown\", \"drop-down\", \"DropDown\", etc."]}], "variables": [{"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._PUNCTUATION_TRANS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.breadcrumbs._BREADCRUMBS_SEP", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zyte_parsers.br